<2ND_LINE>AM-Synagogue Arson, 1st Ld - Writethru, a0674,0275</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>12-Year-Old Boy Arrested for Arson at Synagogue</HEAD>
<NOTE>Eds: Leads with 4 grafs to UPDATE with arrest of juvenile, search
for others, charges. Picks up 2nd graf pvs, `The fire ...'</NOTE>
<DATELINE>NEW YORK (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A 12-year-old boy was arrested Saturday night
and charged with arson for a fire that nearly destroyed a synagogue
where 15 swastikas also were spray-painted, police said.
   Other youths were still being sought, said a police spokesman,
Sgt. Raymond O'Donnell.
   The youth, whose name was withheld because of his age,
surrendered with a parent to detectives, O'Donnell said.
   He was charged as a juvenile delinquent with arson and burglary
and would be released to his parents for an appearance in family
court at a later date, O'Donnell said.
   The fire, reported early Saturday, started on the main floor of
Orthodox Congregation Rabbinical Institute Sharai Torah in the
borough of Brooklyn, said Sgt. Maurice Howard, a police spokesman.
He said the fire caused extensive interior structural damage.
   ``These people have violated not only the criminal law, they
have violated every law of decency, and people of every religion
have to be horrified that any temple of religion has been
desecrated,'' said Mayor Edward I. Koch.
   Howard said a torah, a parchment scroll containing Scriptures,
was set on fire, and 15 swastikas and some obscenities were
spray-painted on the interior.
   Because the fire and desecration were declared a bias incident,
a task force was formed to investigate the incident.
   The Jewish Community Relations Council said it was offering a
$5,000 reward for information leading to the arrest and indictment
of the arsonists.
</TEXT>
