<HEAD>Emperor Suffering From Fever, Cancels Visit</HEAD>
<DATELINE>TOKYO (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Emperor Hirohito suffered from a mild fever Sunday
that forced him to cancel his visit to the Tokyo sumo arena for the
fall wrestling meet, the Imperial Household Agency reported.
   The 87-year-old emperor had a fever of 100 degrees Fahrenheit on
Sunday morning, and doctors advised him not to attend the matches,
the agency said. It said the emperor's fever dropped to 99 degrees
later in the morning.
   The emperor ``feels well and has a good appetite. He is all
right,'' said an official of the agency, who spoke on condition of
anonymity.
   Doctors said the fever might have been caused by a slight
inflammation of the intestinal tract, according to the official. A
year ago, Hirohito underwent an intestinal bypass operation.
