<DATELINE>WASHINGTON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   When their party regained control of the
Senate two years ago, liberal Democrats placed at the top of their
agenda raising a minimum wage that President Reagan claimed had
``caused more misery and unemployment than anything since the Great
Depression.''
   With only seven weeks remaining until voters pick Reagan's
successor, his former running mate and GOP-designated heir, George
